<p><b>Benjamin Harvey Hill</b> (September 14, 1823 – August 16, 1882) was a <a href="/wiki/United_States_House_of_Representatives" title="United States House of Representatives">U.S. Representative</a>, <a href="/wiki/United_States_Senate" title="United States Senate">U.S. senator</a> and a <a href="/wiki/Confederate_States_Senate" title="Confederate States Senate" class="mw-redirect">Confederate senator</a> from the <a href="/wiki/U.S._state" title="U.S. state">state</a> of <a href="/wiki/Georgia_(U.S._state)" title="Georgia (U.S. state)">Georgia</a>.</p>
<p></p>
